Segmentation:

The market is divided into three categories: transportation fuel, natural gas grid feeding, and electricity and heat generating. By 2029, the sector that produces electricity and heat is anticipated to have the biggest market share. The demand for biogas for the production of electricity has increased significantly as a result of the increased focus on renewable energy, particularly in the electric power sector. In the United States, approximately 1 billion kWh of power was produced by industrial and sewage wastewater treatment facilities in 2021, compared to around 220 million kWh of energy produced using biogas (from 24 cattle and dairy firms). The state Renewable Power Standards categorise biogas as a renewable energy source that may be used to produce power throughout the nation (RES).

